<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,500]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,306,296,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
. Because of the relative scarcity of sediment particles on the body, 
<taxonomicName box="[1056,1256,296,320]" class="Polychaeta" family="Flabelligeridae" genus="Piromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brisegnoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1056,1256,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Piromis brisegnoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1262,1325,296,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1262,1325,296,320]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is closely allied with 
<taxonomicName box="[280,428,333,356]" class="Polychaeta" family="Flabelligeridae" genus="Piromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="amoureuxi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[280,428,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. amoureuxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[437,501,332,356]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[437,501,332,356]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, a Caribbean Sea species. The two species differ especially in chaetal features: 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Flabelligeridae" genus="Piromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brisegnoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. brisegnoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[268,334,368,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[268,334,368,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has longer notochaetae (about 
<number box="[703,713,367,391]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[723,739,367,391]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2.0">2</number>
as long vs 
<number box="[880,890,367,391]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[901,915,367,391]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="3.0">3</number>
as long as body width), and more abundant notochaetae (about 
<number box="[371,399,404,428]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="10.0">10</number>
vs 
<number box="[440,481,404,428]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
per bundle); the distal neurochaetal article in 
<taxonomicName box="[1002,1136,404,428]" class="Polychaeta" family="Flabelligeridae" genus="Piromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brisegnoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1002,1136,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. brisegnoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1143,1206,404,428]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1143,1206,404,428]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is falcate and tapering, while it is straight and of about the same width in 
<taxonomicName box="[761,908,441,464]" class="Polychaeta" family="Flabelligeridae" genus="Piromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="amoureuxi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[761,908,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. amoureuxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[914,977,440,464]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[914,977,440,464]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
